{"cursor":"1414","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Openness' may also refers to a very general philosophical position from which\nsome individuals and organizations operate, often highlighted by a decision-\nmaking process recognizing communal management by distributed stakeholders\n(users, producers, or contributors) rather than a centralized authority (owners,\nexperts, boards of directors, etc.).\n\nOpenness could be a synonym of :\n* Open system : Openness to experience, wiki, direct democracy, open\n  spirituality, respect for all other beings, etc. (fully open)\n* Transparency : openness in a utilitarian view : economical openness, open\n  economic or politic data, etc. (lower degree of openness)\n","linknr":116,"url":"Openness","recorded":1362567615,"links":20,"instances":["humanities","systems_theory","learning_theory","publishing"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Open methodologies|"],"headings":["References","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg/40px-Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["open_system","systems_theory"],["transparency","behavior"],["transparency","humanities"],["connectivism","learning_theory"],["open_access","publishing"],["open_system","systems_theory"]],"members":["transparency","open_system","connectivism","open_access"],"related":["Philosophical_position","Community","Open_system_(systems_theory)","Openness_to_experience","Wiki","Direct_democracy","Transparency_(behavior)","Umberto_Eco","Transparency_(humanities)","Connec